    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-06-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="771"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d771">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">411.12 Gomez and Rubio/49</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Mexican Chargé</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrera de Huerta</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-24">June 24,
                            1931</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The receipt is acknowledged of your note of June
                    16, 1931,<note n="16" xml:id="d771fn16">Not printed.</note> with further
                    reference to the unfortunate shooting at Ardmore, Oklahoma, of the young Mexican
                    students, Emilio Cortés Rubio and Manuel García Gómez. You inform the Department
                    that the Ministry of Foreign Relations of Mexico considers it desirable that the
                    necessary investigations be continued by the Governor of the State of
                    Oklahoma.</p>
                <pb facs="0837" n="717" xml:id="pg_717"/>
                <p>According to the Department’s information, the authorities of the State of
                    Oklahoma are pursuing the investigation of this case with all due despatch
                    required by law.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James Grafton Rogers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
